UniCredit, Tenaris, Fiat: Italian Market Equity Preview

-- B y   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 
2011-02-25T07:15:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/unicredit-tenaris-fiat-italian-market-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Italian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  Italy’s benchmark  FTSE MIB Index  rose 18.94, or 0.1
percent, to 21,948.73 in Milan.    UniCredit SpA  (UCG IM): Italy’s competition regulator
approved the purchase of UniCredit MedioCredito Centrale SpA by
Poste Italiane, according to a statement posted on the
regulator’s website.  Poste Italiane  is buying 100 percent of the
bank. UniCredit slid 0.5 percent to 1.84 euros.  Tenaris SpA (TEN IM): The world’s largest maker of seamless
pipes, expects large oil producers to increase their investments
this year, Chief Executive Officer Paolo Rocca said in a
conference call. Tenaris eastern hemisphere area manager
Alejandro Lammertyn said the company had “some” delays in
shipments from Egypt. Tenaris fourth-quarter profit rose 44
percent on higher sales. The shares dropped 3.9 percent to 16.34
euros.  Fiat SpA (F IM): Standard & Poor’s Ratings Services said it
lowered its long-term corporate credit rating on  Fiat SpA  to BB
from BB+. The outlook is negative, S&P said. The stock rose 0.1
percent to 6.70 euros.    Telecom Italia SpA  (TIT IM): Italy’s biggest phone company
said today that it expects a 15 percent annual increase in its
dividend through 2013. The company reported 2010 net income of
3.12 billion euros late yesterday.  The stock fell 0.1 percent
to 1.05 euros.  -- Editor: Jerrold Colten  To contact the reporter on this story:
